{"content":"<p class=\"ql-align-justify\">Suffering Souls triumphantly return to the symphonic black metal scene with their latest release, “An Iconic Taste of Demise”. The album, written entirely by Tobias “Lord Esgaroth” Micko, showcases an evolution in their sound that is both aggressive and expansive, setting a new standard in their already illustrious career.</p><p class='lead'><br></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong>Where Ferocity Collides with Sophistication</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">“An Iconic Taste of Demise” exudes an intriguing vibe. Each track reflects the meticulous craftsmanship and passion that Lord Esgaroth has poured into the project. From the infernal depths of “Soul Devourer”, with its relentless barrage of ferocious riffs and soul-crushing vocals, to the haunting beauty of the instrumental pieces “Of Clarity and Hysteria” and “Cruelty in Love and Fear”, the 56-minute opus showcases a relentless blend of orchestral elements and brutal black metal.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">The album’s lyrics delve into themes of existential anguish, religious blasphemy, and the dark side of human nature. Tracks like “Dolor Matris” paint a vivid picture of suffering and despair, while others, such as “From Hubris to Demise” explore the destructive consequences of arrogance and pride. Each song is a skillfully crafted narrative, drawing listeners deeper into the twisted world of Suffering Souls.</p><p class='lead'><br></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong>Legacy Solidified</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">With “An Iconic Taste of Demise”, the band members solidify their legacy as veterans and innovators in the symphonic black metal genre. Fans of the band will find this album to be an essential addition to their collection, while newcomers will be captivated by its raw power and emotional depth. In an industry rife with imitation and mediocrity, the members of Suffering Souls emerge as genuine artists, relentlessly pushing the limits of their craft and leaving an enduring impact on the metal landscape. Recorded at the legendary Hertz Studio in Poland, the album benefits from top-tier production, enhancing its sonic intensity and ensuring a truly immersive listening experience.</p>","title":"ALBUM REVIEW: Suffering Souls’ “An Iconic Taste of Demise” — Aggression Meets Elegance","details":"Idolum [2.00]; Soul Devourer [06:24]; From Hubris to Demise [05:51]; In the Order of Doom [05:43]; Dolor Matris [05:52]; A Touch of Evil Kindness [06:21]; Under My Skin [05:27]; My Whore [05:03]; Of Clarity and Hysteria [04:50]; Cruelty in Love and Fear [07:59].","Socials":"\n<p class='lead'>\n  <a href='https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100063490099366'><i class='bi bi-facebook'></i></a>\n  <a href='https://www.instagram.com/suffering_souls_official?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAAR3vybhhN5GqZfbo3Fy3Gnab6ReJvimj35sx4EkyKgikBQ8VSKFSOWAm8XQ_aem_AYbkhFY_hyovFnSNdsxIlCLyZ3cwPh3kx6NzHirukbq_7Oe4RlaVc_XQ1MC3ioyTwQOV5FtB9EdpJuEADCYy6yT_'><i class='bi bi-instagram'></i></a>\n  <a href='https://open.spotify.com/album/5YFV0i1KwZAZJ2EZXgbzwN'><i class='bi bi-spotify'></i></a>\n  <a href='https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCapUAZ_bKCGM8TEuHX-Iniw'><i class='bi bi-youtube'></i></a>\n</p>","img01":"https://pulse-of-the-underground.com/assets/Suffering_Souls.jpeg","sub":"gbK4OvgKbyYDfYCfIjboOqjA9Yv1","date":"31/05/2024","lang":"en","translations":{"en":"ALBUM-REVIEW-Suffering-Souls-An-Iconic-Taste-of-Demise---Aggression-Meets-Elegance.json"},"category":"Latest Reviews(ENG)","isReady":true}